LEPTOSPIROSIS - FRANCE (OCCITANIE) WATERSPORTS, ARGENSOU CANYON, ALERT
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 15 Aug 2021 15:37 CEST
Source: France3 [in French, machine trans., edited]
https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/occitanie/ariege/foix/ariege-alerte-a-la-leptospirose-dans-le-canyon-de-l-argensou-sur-la-commune-d-auzat-2214661.html


Following the discovery of a case of leptospirosis in a person who descended the Argensou canyon in Ariege [Occitanie], analysis results are awaited. But an order should be issued this Monday [16 Aug 2021] by the mayor of Auzat to prohibit access to the site.

The Haute-Montagne gendarmerie platoon (PGHM) of Ariege is warning canyoning enthusiasts this Sunday [15 Aug 2021]. Indeed, a person who has crossed this canyon contracted leptospirosis, a bacterial disease most frequently transmitted by the urine of rodents, in particular rats. In humans, the disease is often mild but can lead to kidney failure. It is fatal in 5 to 20% of cases.

Another 2 people who have been in the canyon are currently awaiting the results of their analyzes. The mayor of Auzat should issue an order on [Mon 16 Aug 2021] to ban swimming in this area.

For their part, the gendarmes ask summer visitors not to swim temporarily in the Argensou canyon while awaiting the results of the water analyzes which should be carried out.

[Byline: Christine Ravier]

--
Communicated by:
Mahmoud Orabi
